Q1.:-  Explain Layered Architecture in Business application?

Answer:- In Business Application Layered Architecture is divided into 3 layers:-

         1) Presentation Layer:- It is a set of java classes, Which are responsible for generating 
            user input screen and response page(output screen) is known as presentation Layer.
            This Layer provides the interaction with the end user.
            
         2)Business Logic Layer/Service Layer:-
           Implementation of business rule of a business organization is known as business Logic.
           It is a collection of java classes whose methods have business logic to process the 
           data according to the business rules.
           
           
         3)Data Access Layer:- A set of java classes whose methods are exclusively meant for performing
            CRUD operation with the Data Base server using JDBC and DAO pattern is known as Data 
            Access Layer.
             
